external_knowledge:
- Average production per hectare is a measure of crop yield per unit of land area, indicating the productivity of the land; 
- Water usage efficiency is a measure of how well the actual water used for irrigation matches the optimal water requirements of the crop, indicating the effectiveness of water management;
- Pest control and disease control measures are important factors in crop management, indicating the efforts made to prevent damage to crops from pests and diseases.

